{{Infobox person | name = Al Kikume | image = Al Kikume.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Kikume in ''[[Bela Lugosi Meets a Brooklyn Gorilla]]'', 1952 | birthname = Elmer Kikume Gozier | birth_date = {{birth date|1894|10|9}} | birth_place = [[Honolulu, Hawaii]] or [[Kansas]], U.S. | death_date = {{death date and age|1972|3|27|1894|10|9}} | death_place = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S. | othername = | occupation =Actor, stuntman | yearsactive = 1933&ndash;1954 | spouse = {{marriage|Virgil Smith|1916|1925}} | website = }} '''Al Kikume''' (9 October 1894 &ndash; 27 March 1972), born '''Elmer Kikume Gozier''', was an American actor and [[stuntman]] of [[Native Hawaiians|Hawaiian]] descent. He was born in either [[Honolulu, Hawaii|Honolulu]] or [[Kansas]] and died in [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]]. Beginning with his first credited role, in the independently produced ''[[Tarzan the Fearless]]'' (1933), Kikume was a regular performer in Hollywood jungle movies during the 1930s, 1940s and 1950s.
