{{Use Indian English|date=July 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}} {{BLP sources|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Jaya Bhattacharya | image = Jaya Bhattacharya.jpg | image_size = 220 | alt = | caption = Battacharya at the 2010 Zee Rishtey Awards | native_name = জয়া ভট্টাচাৰ্য্য | native_name_lang = as | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1971|09|19}} | birth_place = [[Guwahati]], [[Assam]], [[India]] | nationality = [[India]]n | other_names = | occupation = [[Television actress]] | known_for = ''[[Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi]]'', ''[[Thapki Pyar Ki]]'' }}
'''Jaya Battacharya''' is an [[India]]n [[television]] actress. She is known for playing antagonistic roles in TV serials. She has also done small roles in movies. Best known for playing Payal in soap opera ''[[Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi]]'', she also played the roles of Jigyasa Bali in ''[[Kasamh Se]]'', Sakku Bai in [[Jhansi Ki Rani (TV series)|''Jhansi Ki Rani'']], and Sudha Buaa in ''[[Gangaa]]''. She again gained popularity with her role of Vasundhara Pandey in drama series ''[[Thapki Pyar Ki]]'' (2015–2017). She appears on ''[[Silsila Badalte Rishton Ka]]'' (2018–present).
==Acting career== She played minor roles in Bollywood films [[Devdas (2002 Hindi film)|''Devdas'']] and ''[[Lajja (2001 film)|Lajja]].'' She also appeared on television with shows like ''[[Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi]]'', playing Payal,<ref>{{cite news |title=Jolly good Jaya! |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/587372.cms |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=2006-11-26 |accessdate=2008-03-22 }}</ref> and ''[[Banoo Main Teri Dulhan]]''. Bhattacharya was given a cameo appearance in the 2000's Hindi film ''[[Fiza]]'', starring [[Karisma Kapoor]]''.''<ref>{{cite news|title=Jaya Bhattacharya's new avatar |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/television/top-stories/news/jaya-banoo-main-teri-dulhan-300807.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120708074953/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/television/top-stories/news/jaya-banoo-main-teri-dulhan-300807.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2012-07-08 |work=Entertainment One India |date=2007-08-30 |accessdate=2008-03-22 }}</ref> She has also worked in the film ''[[Jigyaasa]]'' where she played a filmmaker who wants to make a documentary on a controversial actress. This character was similar to the [[Alice Patten]]'s role in the Indian movie ''[[Rang De Basanti]]''. She has also acted in ''[[Kasamh Se]]'' as Jigyasa in 2007, replacing the regular actor in the same role.
Bhattacharya was seen in the avatar of Sakku Bai in historical series [[Jhansi Ki Rani (TV series)|''Jhansi Ki Rani'']] on Zee TV. She joined the romantic soap opera ''[[Thapki Pyar Ki]]'' in the prominent supporting character of Vasundhara Pandey; the show aired between 2015–2017. In 2018, she entered the hit show ''[[Badho Bahu]]'' as a social worker Sushma Bua.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.freepressjournal.in/entertainment/tv-actress-jaya-bhattacharya-to-enter-hit-show-badho-bahu/1269222|title=TV actress Jaya Bhattacharya to enter hit show 'Badho Bahu' {{!}} Free Press Journal|date=2018-05-02|work=Free Press Journal|access-date=2018-07-14|language=en-GB}}</ref>
