Abū Bakrah ibn Kaladah ath-Thaqafī aṭ-Ṭā’ifī ({{lang-ar|أَبُـو بَـكْـرَة ابْـن كَـلَـدَة الـثَّـقَـفِي الـطَّـائِـفِي}}) better known as '''Nufay‘ ibn Al-Ḥārith''' ({{lang-ar|نُـفَـيْـع ابْـن الْـحَـارِث}}) was the half brother of [[Nafi ibn al-Harith]].<ref name="Haddad1005">{{citation |last=Haddad |first=G. F. |title=Abu Bakrah and the Feminists |publisher=''Abc.se'' |url=https://www.abc.se/~m9783/o/abfm_e.html |date=2005-01-15 |access-date=}}</ref>

He is known for his dispute  with another Islamic general [[Mugheera ibn Shuba]] during a military expedition.

