{{notability|date=June 2018}} [[Image:Shawn Decker.jpg|thumb|195px|right|Shawn Decker]]'''Shawn Decker''' was born in [[Waynesboro, Virginia]] on July 16, 1975. He was diagnosed with [[HIV]] at age 11, through the use of tainted blood products used to treat [[hemophilia]], a bleeding disorder that he was born with. In 1996, he posted a web site called "My Pet Virus", writing humorous articles about himself and blogging about life with HIV. He befriended fellow "poz blogger" [[Steve Schalchlin]], as well as [[POZ (magazine)|POZ magazine]], who turned his [[blog]] into a regular column the following year, called "Positoid", a word that Decker made up to describe himself as [[HIV positive people|someone living with HIV]].
His memoir, ''My Pet Virus, The True Story of a Rebel Without a Cure'' was published in 2006.<ref>{{cite news |title= What's so funny? |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/c/a/2006/09/28/NSGIBJI95P1.DTL&type=printable |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |date=2006-09-28 |accessdate=2008-03-21 | first=Ragnar | last=Carlson}}</ref>
